cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

This paper proposes a novel curriculum learning algorithm for training generative models, which is a topic closely related to machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments are conducted on image datasets, specifically cat and human-face data, which suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) is also a relevant sub-category. The algorithm involves clustering, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the active set, which is a concept related to neural networks (cs.NE) and the geometric analysis, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS).
